The paper discusses the use of deep learning algorithms for anomaly detection, specifically autoencoders, which are commonly used in the subfield of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also mentions the use of SHAP, a game theory-based framework, which is commonly used in the subfield of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper uses real-world data and visually depicts features, which suggests the use of computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses the challenge of manual validation of results, which is a common issue in the subfield of computer security (cs.CR). Finally, the paper mentions the use of outlier detection algorithms, which is a topic commonly studied in the subfield of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS).
